  <!-- NY Workers' Comp Requirements -->
  <section class="py-20 bg-gray-50">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="text-center mb-12">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">New York Workers' Compensation Requirements</h2>
        <p class="text-xl text-gray-600">
          What Albany employers need to know
        </p>
      </div>
      
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-8 max-w-5xl mx-auto">
        <div class="bg-white p-8 rounded-lg shadow-lg">
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-4">When It's Required</h3>
          <ul class="space-y-3 text-gray-600">
            <li class="flex items-start">
              <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-navy-600 mt-0.5 mr-2 flex-shrink-0" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M9 12l2 2 4-4m6 2a9 9 0 11-18 0 9 9 0 0118 0z"></path>
              </svg>
              <span><strong>1 or more employees</strong> in NY (including part-time)</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start">
              <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-navy-600 mt-0.5 mr-2 flex-shrink-0" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M9 12l2 2 4-4m6 2a9 9 0 11-18 0 9 9 0 0118 0z"></path>
              </svg>
              <span>Sole proprietors and partners must carry coverage if they employ others</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start">
              <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-navy-600 mt-0.5 mr-2 flex-shrink-0" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M9 12l2 2 4-4m6 2a9 9 0 11-18 0 9 9 0 0118 0z"></path>
              </svg>
              <span>Required for state contractors and Albany construction contractors</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start">
              <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-navy-600 mt-0.5 mr-2 flex-shrink-0" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M9 12l2 2 4-4m6 2a9 9 0 11-18 0 9 9 0 0118 0z"></path>
              </svg>
              <span>Coverage required from day one—before the first employee starts work</span>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white p-8 rounded-lg shadow-lg">
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-4">Penalties for Non-Compliance</h3>
          <ul class="space-y-3 text-gray-600">
            <li class="flex items-start">
              <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-red-600 mt-0.5 mr-2 flex-shrink-0" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M12 9v2m0 4h.01m-6.938 4h13.856c1.54 0 2.502-1.667 1.732-3L13.732 4c-.77-1.333-2.694-1.333-3.464 0L3.34 16c-.77 1.333.192 3 1.732 3z"></path>
              </svg>
              <span><strong>Fines up to $2,000</strong> per 10-day period without coverage</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start">
              <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-red-600 mt-0.5 mr-2 flex-shrink-0" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M12 9v2m0 4h.01m-6.938 4h13.856c1.54 0 2.502-1.667 1.732-3L13.732 4c-.77-1.333-2.694-1.333-3.464 0L3.34 16c-.77 1.333.192 3 1.732 3z"></path>
              </svg>
              <span>Immediate <strong>stop-work orders</strong></span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start">
              <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-red-600 mt-0.5 mr-2 flex-shrink-0" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M12 9v2m0 4h.01m-6.938 4h13.856c1.54 0 2.502-1.667 1.732-3L13.732 4c-.77-1.333-2.694-1.333-3.464 0L3.34 16c-.77 1.333.192 3 1.732 3z"></path>
              </svg>
              <span>Personal liability for all medical costs and lost wages</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start">
              <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-red-600 mt-0.5 mr-2 flex-shrink-0" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M12 9v2m0 4h.01m-6.938 4h13.856c1.54 0 2.502-1.667 1.732-3L13.732 4c-.77-1.333-2.694-1.333-3.464 0L3.34 16c-.77 1.333.192 3 1.732 3z"></path>
              </svg>
              <span>Potential <strong>criminal charges</strong> for willful non-compliance</span>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="mt-12 bg-blue-50 border-l-4 border-blue-400 p-6 max-w-3xl mx-auto">
        <p class="text-gray-700">
          <strong>Albany Business Tip:</strong> The NY Workers' Compensation Board, based in Albany, actively monitors compliance statewide. Don't risk your business—get covered today. We can provide same-day certificates for urgent state contract needs.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Local FAQ -->
  <section class="py-20">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="text-center mb-12">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">Albany Workers' Comp Questions</h2>
        <p class="text-xl text-gray-600">
          Common questions from Capital Region employers
        </p>
      </div>
      
      <div class="space-y-6">
        <details class="bg-white rounded-lg shadow-lg p-6 cursor-pointer hover:shadow-xl transition-shadow duration-200">
          <summary class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 cursor-pointer">
            How much does workers' comp cost for Albany businesses?
          </summary>
          <p class="mt-4 text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">
            For Albany employers, workers' comp costs typically range from <strong>$1-$2 per $100 of payroll</strong> for low-risk businesses (offices, professional services) to <strong>$5-$15 per $100</strong> for high-risk industries (construction, manufacturing). Your exact rate depends on your industry classification, payroll, and claims history.
          </p>
        </details>

        <details class="bg-white rounded-lg shadow-lg p-6 cursor-pointer hover:shadow-xl transition-shadow duration-200">
          <summary class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 cursor-pointer">
            Do government contractors need special coverage?
          </summary>
          <p class="mt-4 text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">
            New York State contracts typically require proof of workers' compensation coverage <strong>before contract execution</strong>. Many state agencies also require specific certificate language. We understand these requirements and can provide compliant certificates quickly for Albany-area government contractors.
          </p>
        </details>

        <details class="bg-white rounded-lg shadow-lg p-6 cursor-pointer hover:shadow-xl transition-shadow duration-200">
          <summary class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 cursor-pointer">
            Do I need workers' comp for interns or co-op students?
          </summary>
          <p class="mt-4 text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">
            If interns or co-op students (including from UAlbany, RPI, or other local colleges) receive <strong>any form of compensation</strong> as W-2 employees, they must be covered. Unpaid interns may not require coverage, but consult with us to ensure compliance with NY requirements.
          </p>
        </details>

        <details class="bg-white rounded-lg shadow-lg p-6 cursor-pointer hover:shadow-xl transition-shadow duration-200">
          <summary class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 cursor-pointer">
            Are remote employees covered?
          </summary>
          <p class="mt-4 text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">
            Yes. Your NY workers' compensation policy covers <strong>remote employees</strong> working from home in New York State for injuries that occur during work activities. This is important for Albany's growing tech and professional sectors with hybrid/remote workers.
          </p>
        </details>

        <details class="bg-white rounded-lg shadow-lg p-6 cursor-pointer hover:shadow-xl transition-shadow duration-200">
          <summary class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 cursor-pointer">
            How quickly can I get a certificate of insurance?
          </summary>
          <p class="mt-4 text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">
            PCFG Insurance can often provide <strong>same-day certificates of insurance</strong> for Albany businesses. This is critical when you need proof of coverage for state contracts, construction permits, or vendor requirements. Contact us by 2 PM for same-day issuance with proper state contract language if needed.
          </p>
        </details>
      </div>

      <div class="mt-12 text-center">
        <p class="text-gray-600 mb-4">Ready to protect your Albany business?</p>
        <a href="#quote-form" class="inline-block bg-navy-600 hover:bg-navy-700 text-white px-8 py-3 rounded-md font-semibold transition-colors duration-200">
          Get Your Free Albany Quote
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

